OL,3,CThird of buyers 'experienced scam on
OL,4,Csecond-hand marketplaces in last two
OL,5,Cyears'
OL,7,FTypically, buyers who had experienced
OL,8,Fa scam reported receiving incorrect
OL,9,Fgoods (15%) or no goods at all (15%),
OL,10,Fwhile 11% had received an empty
OL,11,Fpackage and 10% had received
OL,12,Fcounterfeit goods.
OL,14,FPurchase scams were the most common
OL,15,Fform of authorised push payment fraud,
OL,16,Faccounting for 66% of all cases
OL,17,Freported to banks, according to the
OL,18,Flatest UK Finance data.
